**Segments**

- **By Product Type**: The CRISPR gene-editing market can be segmented into CRISPR enzymes, kits & reagents, and others. CRISPR enzymes, such as Cas9, Cas12, and Cas13, play a pivotal role in gene editing by cutting DNA at precise locations. Kits & reagents are essential components used for conducting CRISPR experiments effectively.

- **By Application**: The market can be segmented based on applications into genetic engineering, gene library construction, CRISPR plasmid construction, human stem cells, and others. Genetic engineering applications involve the modification of genes in organisms for various purposes such as biotechnology, agriculture, and medicine.

- **By End-User**: This segment comprises of biotechnology & pharmaceutical companies, academic & research institutions, contract research organizations (CROs), and others. Biotechnology & pharmaceutical companies are major users of CRISPR technology for drug discovery, development, and treatment of genetic disorders.

